  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Peel and deseed the squash. If you would like some ideas for what to do with the skin and seeds, check out the other squash recipes on site."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cut the squash into 1cm cubes. Mince the garlic. Wash and grate the ginger, you don't need to peel it."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat a large pot over medium heat. Once hot, add oil, onions, ginger and garlic. Sauté for 2 minutes, stirring frequently. Add the butternut squash and season with salt, pepper, and curry powder. Stir to coat well. Then cover and cook for 4 mins, stirring occasionally. Add coconut milk, peanut butter, and vegetable stock. Bring to a low boil over medium heat and then reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 15 mins or until butternut squash is fork tender."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "While the soup is simmering, cook the tofu. Drain the tofu and pat it dry. Cut it into 2cm cubes. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Once hot, add the tofu and fry for 3-4 mins until it starts to brown. Add the soy sauce, sesame seeds and coconut, if using. Fry for another minute and remove from the heat."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Use an immersion blender, or transfer soup to a blender, and purée on high until creamy and smooth. If using a blender, return soup back to pot.\nTaste and adjust seasonings, adding more curry powder, salt, or sweetener as needed. Continue cooking for a few more minutes over medium heat."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cook your udon noodles according to package instructions."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To serve, pour the soup into a large bowl, add the noodles and top with the tofu. Scatter some more sesame seeds, coconut coconut and fresh chilli and coriander."
    }
  ],
